      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Fabulist</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brian Leung letter comments on Deborah Solomon's April 8 interview with writer Nathan Englander</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Nathan Englander's coolness in the face of questioning about why he hasn't published a book in eight years was refreshing (Deborah Solomon, April 8). If more editors and more writers agreed that it's healthy to take time between books, the shelves at bookstores would be stocked with fewer, but undoubtedly better, books.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
